com.i2group.apollo.commandservice.transport

Class MergeEntities

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.i2group.apollo.commandservice.transport.Command
      • com.i2group.apollo.commandservice.transport.MergeEntities
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ICommand

    public final class MergeEntities
extends Command
    The ICommand for merging one or more source Entitys into a target Entity.

    Leasing:

    • An active lease must exist on the Entity that is the target in the merge operation.
    • Active leases must exist on all the Entitys that are sources in the merge operation.
    Authorization:
    • The current user must have the SecurityAccessLevel.UPDATE access level for the Entity that is the target in the merge operation.
    • The current user must have the SecurityAccessLevel.UPDATE access level for all the Entitys that are sources in the merge operation.
    Validation:
    • All of the Entitys involved in the merge operation must have the same EntityType.
    • The target Entity must not be the same as any of the source Entitys.
    • The target Entity must not have ProhibitedEdit associated with its EntityType.
    • No two source Entitys must be the same.
    • None of the source Entitys must own a set.
    • It is not possible to merge Entitys in the same CommandList as an AddLatestItemsToSet, AddSpecificItemsToSet, or RemoveItemsFromSet command.
    Since:
    4.0
